	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, May 16th 7:17 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.55]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well from my point of view you are as a bard expected to be able to do all things. Since you are the jack of all trades, you must fill the missing person (ie enchanter, druid aso)<br><br>So set up your songs after how the group is made.<br>If you no snarer..be sure to use your snare song. If you have one but not a slower...switch to a song that slows but dosent overwrite snare. <br><br>If you are grouped with alot of melees and no healers try charm kiting if possible and grab you instrument instead of meleeing.Just doing hp/speed/slow songs<br><br>If you mainly have casters then only use mana song and forget about hastes and such..do melee but keep playing mana (boring but the casters have way more benefit of you doing that than you twisting songs for you and the warrior to get 14 hps regain and get a lil more speed.<br><br>I agree many people well either tell you to act different than you are do or complain about you not playing mana all the time. <br><br>In most matter this comes out of lack of knowledges about bards abilities. Tell them what you are playing and why.. and they might realise that you are not just a manasinger after all<br><br>My 2 cents<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Cyrix<br>60 Bard<br>Test</td></tr>
