	   <tr><td colspan=2>in this order: dex, cha, agi or str<br><br>although i didn't put any points into cha at startup, since i didn't know much, mine has been somewhat low becuz of it. however i managed to get hold of a few jewelry items to up these points to 120 or so and i have barely any probs when charming (i charm over mez). dex affects fizzle rate of songs, learning melee skills, and proccing weps (not as important till later lvls). agi to help lessen the dmg when ya get hit or avoid being hit altogether. str to hold some plate and other items and for melee combat, or whatever you wanna call bardic melee.<br><br>as for the armor, you can't start questing for lambent till late 20s or you got areally helpful higher lvl friend to multi-quest it for you. get some banded armor from a blacksmith who could use the business. banded runs at 1pp per AC, which is not overly xpensive since if you sell everything you looted to lvl you up, you should have a good 5pp for so to get you started. when you get 8-9 go to EC and fight at the orc camps in a grp. sell the belts to other players at 2-3pp each and finish your banded set. if your on Saryrn, send a tell i'll see what i can do.<br><br>Taamas Starsinger<br>40th Season<br>House of Wargoth<br>Saryrn<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
