	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have a 37 bard on Bertoxx, and I'm pretty happy with his stats so far. You'll need a decent CHA, cause charm is one of the best things about being a bard, and you need high CHA for charm to stick. Also, you'll want a decent DEX for raising melee skills and proccing those weapons at high levels. STR probably comes after that - cause you're melee and you need to be able to deal damage. As a bard, you're an INT caster, but don't worry about INT too much, as you'll rarely use mana cause most of your spells are free :)<br>As for armor, like every other class - scrounge for what you can get. Lambent if you can get it, if not I'd go with banded, cause you're really not strong enough for full bronze.<br><br>Hope this helps ) <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
