	   <tr><td colspan=2>cha affects our minding altering songs - the mez and charm songs. it is bascially mandatory doing crowd control when a chanter is not present, since no other class can. think bout it - why would you have a mob beatin on your tank using up valuable mana from the healer who is doin double time healin cuz of the extra mob, then just not attackin and keeping the darn thing mezzed or even better charm it. its always nice to see a mob fightin his bro. i have something like 120 cha and i only get resisted bout 15% of time im guessing, reds i can charm wit 40% resists. if you got the skills and know how to charm, make it attack his bro then reapply charm WHILE using chains and attackin the other one, i feel you've filled your role as crowd control xpertise.  =)  thats xactly what i do, and its worth it after the battle is over and the grp says "that was awesome, thnxs man". then i just thank the cleric cuz i'd be dead witout him/her since after charm wears off, the mob is PISSED at you. so make sure you time it right wit takin less dmg as possible to help cleric healin the tank. heres what i do:<br><br>1) charm<br>2) switch to main mob or just hit assist button<br>3) attack and hit hotkey to make pet attack (/pet attack)<br>4) hit 4 then 4 again (for me its stops charm and starts chain)<br>5) right when chain hits i switch back to pet and hit charm<br><br>i usually time it just right that the mob usually only gets one hit on me after hes uncharmed. your skills will increase as you grow up, your grp will notice and praise you. maybe even safe your life  =)<br><br>Taamas Starsinger<br>40th Season<br>House of Wargoth<br>Saryrn<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
